        timestamp - Time in milliseconds from the beginning of the inventory.
        rssi - Received Signal Strength Indicator, RSSI.
        scaledRssi - Scaled RSSI, 0...100%.

        pc - Protocol Control (PC) bits that the tag backscattered.
        channel - The channel number the tag was last inventoried in, zero based index.
        antennaId - The source tag where the tag was last seen.
        epc - EPC of the tag.

      • customExchange

        public NurRespCustomExchange customExchange(int passwd,
                                            boolean secured,
                                            CustomExchangeParams params)
                                     throws java.lang.Exception
        Do custom bit stream exchange using the tag's EPC for selection and password for access if required. NOTE: a response to this command may be null with successful call. This is the case when the tag only replies with its handle and in the exchange parameters the handle stripping is set to true. In such a situation the module removes the handle thus returning OK but with no data.
        Parameters:
        passwd - Password is required for this operation.
        secured - Set to true is the password is to be used.
        params - The custom exchange parameters.
        Returns:
        When successful returns the custom exchange response.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Can throw exceptions with incorrect parameters or module exchange error.
        See Also:
        NurRespCustomExchange, CustomExchangeParams, customExchange(CustomExchangeParams), NurApi.customExchange(int, int, int, byte[], CustomExchangeParams), NurApi.customExchange(int, boolean, int, int, int, byte[], CustomExchangeParams), NurApi.customExchangeByEpc(byte[], CustomExchangeParams), NurApi.customExchangeByEpc(int, boolean, byte[], CustomExchangeParams)

        public NurRespCustomExchange customExchange(CustomExchangeParams params)
                                     throws java.lang.Exception
        Do custom bit stream exchange using the tag's EPC for selection. NOTE: a response to this command may be null with successful call. This is the case when the tag only replies with its handle and in the exchange parameters the handle stripping is set to true. In such a situation the module removes the handle thus returning OK but with no data.
        Parameters:
        params - The custom exchange parameters.
        Returns:
        When successful returns the custom exchange response.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Can throw exceptions with incorrect parameters or module exchange error.
        See Also:
        NurRespCustomExchange, CustomExchangeParams, customExchange(int, boolean, CustomExchangeParams), NurApi.customExchange(int, int, int, byte[], CustomExchangeParams), NurApi.customExchange(int, boolean, int, int, int, byte[], CustomExchangeParams), NurApi.customExchangeByEpc(byte[], CustomExchangeParams), NOTE: a response to this command may be null with successful call.
